casebody.data:
Dewey Wallace McMURTREY v. Walter A. HUNTER, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 3530. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 12, 1947. Randolph Carpenter, U. S. Atty., and Eugene W. Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, BRATTON, and MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for the reason that order appealed from was not a final or ap-pealable order.
